The need for speed The Run is struggling throughout America.
Revision
Originally a problem-free race is transformed due to a set of stupid mistakes of people who have nothing to do with in a routine morning trip to work.
This fulfills to a certain extent everyone’s ambition but it doesn’t serve anything if no one wants to do something more.
The new part undertitled The Run produced great expectations before its release.
He promised to take a new direction with the already old Need for Speed racing series and to get out a kind of game from playable parts that would not count only with points.
So we were curious how will be the passages added during which the main hero comes out of his car and does what he wants.
As it is already done in the NFS series, the result is completely different than expected.
These are potentially arcade racing games but the set goes down due to some unnecessary errors that have already existed for several years.
These are not really mistakes but rather the expression of an incomprehensible fainity by the developers.
The adventure begins very well.
You are taken into the adventure whose protagonist Jack has characteristic problems and to solve them start to participate in illegal races across America.
You sit behind the wheel on the west coast in San Francisco and your mission is to get the first to New York.
The idea has interesting elements.
The route is divided into ten stages and then more than 50 races.
As a result, each race is done on a different route and the steps planned in different environments that differ quite well from each other and are interesting.
The player does not have the feeling for a single moment that the game offers him something identical.
Some environments are quite beautiful even though the graphic level is the same type as the previous series.
This is not the end of the world.
But driving through the desert, in autumn landscapes or in highly snowed mountains is very pleasant visually.
The trials are more from time to time accumulated with an atypical element.
For example, in the desert you find yourself in a sand storm that sensitively decreases your visibility.
Then in the mountains you need to be careful that an avalanche does not fall on you.
Besides this, the different races are well arranged each other behind each other.
There are only a small number of them, but that is enough.
There are moments you strive to overcome the required number of opponents (as in a classic race) then you run against the clock (classic duel with the chronometer) and then again you are waiting for another duel with an opponent.
From time to time you also have the police who enters the game and who tries to make you the situation difficult.
The new one is out of the vehicle.
This is rather an interactive animation when most of the time Jack escapes in front of someone and you need to help him by typing the right button at the right time.
Nothing complicated.
What is surprising is that there are fewer moments of this type than you expect (to be concrete there are only three).
The result is this because this element is not at risk of disturbing and is placed, in the context described above, in the elements that accumulate the game.
The model of driving is in the tradition of previous games.
This means that there is nothing extraordinary nowadays, but it cannot be said that it is negative.
When it comes to realistic simulation you will have to go to see elsewhere.
But although we can find better in competition the driving model goes very well with the type of race design.
So everything is ok.
Problems begin to appear after a while.
With the differences of the behavior model, the collisions model is not yet to the point.
We don’t expect from this game a complicated deformation and collisions, but when you don’t have, during a collision with any object, any idea of how your car behaves, so it’s not completely good.
During tight overturns you sometimes touch each other slightly but otherwise your car goes into crazy volts.
Or they find themselves in shadows.
Thanks to the restart system this is not really a problem but it really annoys you.
The restart is done in such a way that when you’ve broken your figure or you’ve gone out in the decor the game takes you back at the moment of the last point on the route.
But you only have 5 rebounds.
Once you have used the 5 restartes you have to restart the game from the beginning.
So it’s more a tool, for the case where something doesn’t happen right, than something you can truly rely on.
Sometimes rebounds don’t help and you need to find the solution by remembering the piece of the route in question.
The great hic of this game is that the same actions are found in the same places.
For example, there are some turns that must pass in a certain way, otherwise it does not pass.
Otherwise you meet on a given place of the "civil" vehicles always in the same configuration that you arrive first, fifth, 5 seconds in advance or a minute in delay.
What makes you angry are situations when you see the opponent easily pass between two cars coming in the opposite direction and when you arrive, you have to either put yourself on the side and turn them down or freeze.
It doesn’t matter if you go ahead of him because it’s “calculated”in such a way that for the given situation it always happens close to your nose.
The opponents have other advantages.
During all the time of the game, you get to some places, again without worrying about time, and you always have the same opponent that precedes you in the same place.
This annoys the most at the end of the game when you run on a long bridge in the opposite direction.
The opponent must pass before you at any price.
When he passes in front of you he hides you the sight of the other vehicles in the opposite direction and you get into collision a lot of times.
It can be understood that the goal of this game is to do something fascinating and full of adrenaline,but it is clear that you get bored quickly.
And it’s a shame because through a simple driving model the game is interesting and places with so much action that you don’t have the time to follow everything that’s happening.
And it’s the same if it’s because of the concept of 50 unique routes, that the order of the races is such that there’s no chance to get bored or something else.
The original idea is the car change during the races.
You need to be careful about the petrol pumps on the routes as you can change the car but most of the time the one you have is enough for you.
The cars are divided into three categories.
Sports cars are ideal for cities, big U.S. cylinders for straight highways and super sports cars with exotic trails on very technical routes for example on the lake roads in the mountains.
And the mode of challenges, which are races in particular places you know of the adventure, goes very well with the main regime of the story.
You will not only receive medals but also experience points that add to your profile that is common to challenges and adventure.
When you have reached the highest level of driver, different objects begin to unlock:
This connects online with the Autolog function that among other things compares your achieved results with those of other players and provides you with other functions in the community.
One of the hardest hits to understand is the situation of the last race of the adventure.
You arrive with your car in the metro tunnel (it looks like) where you ride in the dark on the roads (it looks like).
Your speed indicator indicates you between 150 and 200 km/h (a priori) and behind you comes a metro branch that sends you the car directly to the railroad.
At the writing we had a discussion for a few days to see if someone really thought about when creating this game or if the authors really take us as fools.
The technical part of the game is not extra,but the visual part is generally pleasant and in some cases really super.
What annoys is that in more extreme situations, the image does not keep the level and in some cases in a tragic way.
This mainly applies to accidents with a large number of participants when a fluid image is no longer useful to you.
The sound is good and the track is available.
In order to please the greatest number and especially the youngest audience a new soundtrack was created in the style "I mix everything", but we can expect no one to buy the game for music.
Need for Speed: The Run is a big deal.
If the game didn’t have these stupid errors we could say without fear that it’s the best NFS production in recent years.
But this game gives the impression that it is not finished.
The fun is really good but prepare yourself for the mistakes to put you in the eyes with the strength of an airport reflector.
The Students of Velours in concert with the Choirs of Charles University
The Festa Academica festival offers for the third time festivities that connect the International Student Day with the anniversary of the Velours Revolution with a musical part.
During the festival there are 20 chorus of high school and secondary classes.
The festival is composed of two concerts held on November 17th.
“The University of Charles has an important part in this festival.”
“Most among the chorus is the Chorus of the Faculty of Pedagogy and Humanities, in the committee of the festival sits rector Vaclav Hampl,” said organizing team leader Jakub Calou.
The key of the festival is the concert of the Choir of High Schools and Secondary Classes which takes place with free entrance on 17 November from 14 hours on the space located in front of the National Technical Library in Dejvice.
The program includes the composition of the well-known Czech jazzman Karel Ruzicka, Celebration Jazz mass.
In the evening the concert "Students of Velours" takes place in the premises of the National House in Vinohrady during which the chorus of higher schools as well as that of the Charles University take place.
The Festa Academica aims not only to dignely celebrate the International Student Day and to commemorate the 22nd anniversary of the Velours Revolution, but also to present to the public a highest-level chorus music and develop the creative cooperation of young people.
The main organizer is the Union of Czech Pairs in cooperation with the Jan Kepler High School.
All the action is placed under the edge of Bohuslav Svoboda, Mayor of Prague and Vaclav Hampl, Rector of the Charles University.
The festival will take place from 16 to 20 November in Prague and Pardubice.
The program also offers high-level concerts, msical meetings, a student happening and other activities.
Interested people will find all the information on the festival’s internet pages www.festaacademica.cz.
