Steve Jobs continues by giving details about his efforts to simplify accounting at Apple.
Confused about how the costs were recorded – often starting with a “standard cost” assessed by the nose, then adjusted with a “variation” – he developed an automated factory that guaranteed the accurate calculation of commercial costs.
About the opportunity to play a tour to the Pope:
Steve Jobs tells the anecdote of the "Blue Box" he created with Steve Wozniak - a device that served to hack the telephone networks and phone free on a long distance.
The device has been the subject of many previously written, but Steve Jobs’ euphoria here in his description of the Blue Box as an act of ownership is contagious.
