This was the work of the Cali person who identified the body of Alfonso Cano.
A Cali dactyloscopist has passed to history as the man who confirmed the death of 'Alfonso Cano'.
The work of these officials is crucial.
Last November 4 a Dactyloscopist from the CTI of Cali passed to history as the person who confirmed the identity of the Farc's top leader: "Alfonso Cano", facing his fingerprints.
Of the seven dactyloscopists working in the local offices of the CTI, this week it was the turn of “disponibility” of Eliazar González, a man from Puerto Tejada who has been working for 21 years in the field of judicial investigation.
At the beginning of his career, González worked in the municipalities of Chocó, where many times he had to spend more than five days in the forest to get to the place where the bodies were to be identified.
In the year 2000 he was transferred to the capital of Valle and after following appropriate courses, he specialized in dactyloscopy, which is the study of the skin of friction, i.e. the palms and feet.
During the week of the operation against alias Alfonso Cano, Eliazar was warned to take clothes with him for at least three days.
Something great awaited him.
On Friday night he departed to Cauca with a helicopter from Palmira.
He knew that he had to identify two bodies and that one of them was suspected to be the man who led the world's oldest guerrilla, so he was asked to take the map with the ten fingerprints of Guillermo León Sáenz (his true name).
But when he arrived with the investigation team at the place of the body, he didn’t recognize it by his physical appearance, because this was very different from what he had seen in the media.
He didn’t have a barbe, he was dressed like a farmers in the area, without glasses and much weaker.
But the footprints don’t lie.
accompanied by a Gellonian wolf, a ink, a pickup and a lamp, Eliazar compared the fingerprints of the body with those on the map.
His eye did not mistake him: it was "Alfonso Cano".
That same night, the man from Puerto Tejada was the responsible who confirmed to the Defense Minister, Juan Carlos Pinzón that yes, he was the top leader of the FARC.
Looking for the footprint
For a dactyloscopist from Sijín de Cali the recognition that President Juan Manuel Santos made to Eliazar González, at a press conference for the operation against "Cano", is very significant.
Many people don’t know our work.
Dactyloscopy is an accurate, error-free science, which can be crucial in the resolution of crimes.
In addition to identifying the bodies, dactyloscopists support investigations for crimes such as theft and murder and confirm the identity of the people captured.
When captured, many criminals present false identity cards or have no documents.
We take their fingerprints and look for them in the database.
The researcher said that in a case of theft he had to remove a part of the wall of a house, because in that place the thief had pushed his hand to get out a box full of jewelry and money.
"The walls are difficult because they are not adequate surfaces to get a digital footprint, but in this case we were able to get the footprint of all the hands and identify the criminal who had participated in different flights," he recalled.
The fingerprints can also remove or confirm suspects in cases of murder.
Recently, a man was found dead, with bottles of drinks around him.
By means of the investigation it was determined that a parent may be suspected of the crime and in fact a footprint on the bottle coincided.
Even if this does not guarantee that he is the murderer, it puts him on the scene of crime.
A CTI dactyloscopist explained that “the fingerprints of objects are extracted with chemical or physical reactors.”
When they appear, you use a takeover or a band to take them.
Subsequently, the footprints are sent to Asif, the declinquents database, or to the National Civil Registry.
“The problem is that there are still many Colombians without papers,” the CTI expert said.
He explained that everything is not as shown in the CSI television program.
As everything that shines is not gold, everything that is touched does not necessarily become a footprint.
However, it can be used if the confrontation is realized.
