Bray detailed that the response of the 'indignated' to the evacuation of their camp personally dictated by the New York mayor, Michael Bloomberg, arrived to the courts, where judge Lucy Billings issued an order that prohibited the forced evacuation of the place and allowed the protesters to stay in the camp.
Furthermore, the 'indignated' occupied a new park located at the confluence of the Canal Street and the Sixth Avenue, very close to the entrance to the Holland tunnel, which unites New York and New Jersey, property of the parish Trinity Church.
