If the German model, focused on renewable energies, is sometimes presented as an example, reality opposes the speech.
The choice of Berlin will result in the rise in the price of electricity, an energy dependence worsened by the increased use of imported gas, from Russia, a CO2 emissions jump resulting from the construction of gas and coal power plants.
Within a few months, all of these horrible effects are already felt.
